romoney |accessdate=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1993 || Finance Minister of the Year || Asiamoney || || <ref name=\"Mahajan2005\">{{cite book|author=V.S. Mahajan|title=Manmohan S Dream India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DDA5Yk-0Fm4C&pg=PA16|year=2005|publisher=Deep & Deep Publications|isbn=978-81-7629-631-1|pages=16\u2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1986 || Elected National Fellow ||[[National Council of Educational Research and Training|National Institute of Education]]|| || <ref name=\"VEPACHEDU\">{{cite web |title=Prof. Manmohan Singh |url=https://www.vepachedu.org/msingh.html |publisher=Vepachedu Educational Foundation |accessdate=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n|- style=\"background:;\"\n\n| 1985 || Elected President of the Indian Economic Association || Indian Economic Association || || <ref name=\"Vellore\">{{cite web |title=Former Presidents of IEA include former Prime Minister Dr. Manmohan Singh |url=https://vit.ac.in/dr-g-viswanathan-unanimously-elected-indian-economic-association-conference-president |publisher=Vellore Institute of Technology |accessdate=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1982 || Elected Honorary Fellow ||[[St John's College, Cambridge]]|| || <ref name=\"St John\">{{cite web |title=The Dr Manmohan Singh Scholarship |url=https://www.joh.cam.ac.uk/dr-manmohan-singh-scholarship |publisher=St John's College, University of Cambridge |accessdate=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n|- style=\"background:;\"\n\n| 1982 || Elected Honorary Fellow ||[[Indian Institute of Banking and Finance|Indian Institute of Bankers]]|| || <ref name=\"Bankers\">{{cite web |title=About The Author |url=http://www.mea.gov.in/images/main_2007.pdf |publisher=Ministry of External Affairs |accessdate=26 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1976 || Honorary Professorship || [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]] || || <ref name=\"Professorship\">{{cite news |title=School of protest revives professor in PM |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/school-of-protest-revives-professor-in-pm/cid/839301 |accessdate=26 Ap